OL,3,CTories win first Scottish by-election
OL,4,Csince 1967 as SNP vote collapses
OL,6,FThe Conservatives have won their first
OL,7,FScottish by-election in nearly 60
OL,8,Fyears with a "seismic" victory in the
OL,9,FAberdeen South by-election.
OL,11,FDouglas Lumsden won the Aberdeen South
OL,12,Fseat thanks largely to a tactical
OL,13,Fvote, according to Tory sources,
OL,14,Fsecuring 14,308 votes.
OL,16,FMeanwhile, the SNP tally collapsed
OL,17,Ffrom 15,213 in the 2024 general
OL,18,Felection to 8,258 in Thursday's
OL,19,Fcontest.
OL,26,@pD@NOUpD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
